{"lemma": "جَدِيدٌ", "slug": "جَدِيدٌ", "root": "ج.د.د", "root_slug": "ج-د-د", "root_link": "/words/roots/ج-د-د", "pos": "ADJ", "pos_camel": "adj", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "جَدِيد", "root": "جدد", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 8}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["adj"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 1}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n5171"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AF%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "new", "fa": "جدید", "ur": "نیا", "tr": "yeni", "id": "baru", "bn": "নতুন", "es": "nuevo", "fr": "nouveau", "de": "neu", "ru": "новый", "zh": "新的"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "adj", "gloss": "new"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/d͡ʒa.diːd/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n5171", "headword_ar": "جَدِيدٌ", "root": "jd", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faEiylN", "text_ar": "فَعِيلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the sense of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mafoEuwlN", "text_ar": "مَفْعُولٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [i. e. ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "majoduwdN", "text_ar": "مَجْدُودٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Cut,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cut off."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb.) A poet says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "A^abiY Hub~iY sulayomaY A^ano yabiydaA\n                      \n                     \n                        waA^amosaY HaboluhaA xalaqFA jadiydaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "My love of Suleymà hath refused to perish; but her cord"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(i. e. her tie of affection to me)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hath become worn out and cut"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S:) [as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jdyd", "text_ar": "جديد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies “new” more commonly than \"cut,\"] this verse appears as though it involved a contradiction. (MF.) ―         -b2-  Applied to a garment, or a piece"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 387}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of cloth [sufficient for a garment or the like],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Newly cut off"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from the web"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by the weaver:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K:) and so (without"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", S) applied to a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "miloHafap", "text_ar": "مِلْحَفَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, A;) thus applied to a fem. n. because syn. with ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "majoduwdapN", "text_ar": "مَجْدُودَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, ISd;) or, accord. to Sb, because by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mlHfp", "text_ar": "ملحفة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in this case is meant"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_izaAr", "text_ar": "اـِزَار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and for a like reason in like cases; (Ham p. 555;) but one also says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jadiydapN", "text_ar": "جَدِيدَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (ISd;) and accord. to some,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jdyd", "text_ar": "جديد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faEiylN", "text_ar": "فَعِيلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the sense of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faAEilN", "text_ar": "فَاعِلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and therefore the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is regularly affixed to it: (Ham ubi suprà:) the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jududN", "text_ar": "جُدُدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mbr, Th, S, A, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "judadN", "text_ar": "جُدَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (AZ, A'Obeyd, Mbr;) but the former is the more common. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And hence, (L,) applied to a garment, (L, TA,) or a thing, (S, Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "New; contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qadiymN", "text_ar": "قَدِيمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xalaqN", "text_ar": "خَلَقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, L;) from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jid~apN", "text_ar": "جِدَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bilFY", "text_ar": "بِلًى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:) pl. [of pauc.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ajid~apN", "text_ar": "اَجِدَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jududN", "text_ar": "جُدُدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "judadN", "text_ar": "جُدَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (L.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSobaHato xalaquhumo jududFA", "text_ar": "اَصْبَحَتْ خَلَقُهُمْ جُدُدًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", a phrase mentioned by Lh, meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xuloqaAnuhumo jududFA", "text_ar": "خُلْقَانُهُمْ جُدُدًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Their old worn-out garments became replaced by new"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jududFA", "text_ar": "جُدُدًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may be here put for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jadiydFA", "text_ar": "جَدِيدًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (L.) ―         -b4-  And hence, (TA,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AljadiydaAni", "text_ar": "الجَدِيدَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^ajad~aAni", "text_ar": "الاَجَدَّانِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The night and the day;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K;) because they never become impaired by time. (TA.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA A^afoEaluhu maA A@xotalafa AljadiydaAni", "text_ar": "لَا اَفْعَلُهُ مَا ا@خْتَلَفَ الجَدِيدَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^ajad~aAni", "text_ar": "الاَجَدَّانِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I will not do it while the day and the night succeed each other"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA kar~a AljadiydaAni", "text_ar": "مَا كَرَّ الجَدِيدَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^ajad~aAni", "text_ar": "الاَجَدَّانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "while the day and the night return time after time:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ever"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) ―         -b5-  Hence likewise,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jadiydN", "text_ar": "جَدِيدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies A thing"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of which one has had no knowledge."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L.) ―         -b6-  And hence, (L,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aljadiydu", "text_ar": "الجَدِيدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Death:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or is applied as an epithet to death, in the dial. of Hudheyl. (L.) Accord. to Akh and El-Mugháfis El-Báhilee,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jadiydu Almawoti", "text_ar": "جَدِيدُ المَوْتِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The commencement of death."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L.)       -A2-  Also The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "face,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "surface,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the earth, or ground; [as though it were cut;] (S, K, TA;) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jadadN", "text_ar": "جَدَدٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jid~apN", "text_ar": "جِدَّةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jad~N", "text_ar": "جَدٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jid~N", "text_ar": "جِدٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.)       -A3-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jad~N", "text_ar": "جَدٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in two places."}], "source_refs": ["S", "K", "Mbr", "Th", "A", "L", "TA", "Msb"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}